end users or implementing units in the next budgeting period to prepare Project Procurement Management Plan (PPMP) as basis of the budget for the     ensuing year;
the Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) Secretariat to consolidate submitted PPMPs basis in the preparation of the Annual Procurement Plan (APP);
the BAC Secretariat to (i) post procurement activities in the PhilGEPS project’s Notice of Award, Notice to Proceed and Contracts; and (ii) notify             observers in the procurement activities thru bidding:
the General Services Officer to furnish COA copies of all purchase orders/contracts and all papers relative thereto within five (5)  days  after  the  perfection  of the contract and  sending of notification of the time and date of the scheduled deliveries to the Office of the Auditor pursuant to  COA Circular No.            2009-001 and 95-006;
the concerned offices (BAC and Accounting) to submit the required documents as discussed above in accordance with RA No. 9184 and COA Circular No. 2012-001 for further evaluation as basis for the Audit             Team’s subsequent audit action;
require the Municipal Accountant to check the completeness of the required supporting documents for every transaction before any payment is made;
henceforth,  strictly adhere to the laws, rules and regulations governing the procurement of goods pursuant to COA Circular 2012-001 and RIRR of R.A. 9184.

We recommended that the Members of the Local School Board:
Continue to improve a  balanced budget, including for the construction of classrooms and other capital expenditures,  with conscious and concerted efforts of observing compliance with the legal and regulatory requirements on SEF budgeting, allocation and utilization in reference to the abovementioned rules and regulations;
Continue to maximize the utilization of SEF to attain its objectives, monitor the implementation of the PPAs, and take appropriate actions such as realignment  or reprograming, if necessary; and
Comply with the documentary requirements as discussed above, for the evaluation of the Audit Team;
Improve compliance in the documentation of claims to establish their regularity by referring to COA Circular No. 2012-001 for guidance.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
reconstitute an Inventory Committee to include each Department Head to facilitate inventory taking by Office of all the property, plant and equipment of the Municipality;
require the Acting General Services Officer and the Municipal Accountant to (i) maintain Property Records and Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards, respectively, starting with the current year’s acquisition and recent years’ acquisitions and aim for a yearly increase of coverage until all PPE items are covered; (ii) reconcile inventory results with property records and those maintained at the Accounting Office and isolate items not reconciled for easy reference in succeeding inventory taking; (iii) aim to reduce the number and amount of unreconciled PPE account balances;
direct the Acting GSO to prepare Acknowledgement Receipts for Equipment (ARE) for all PPE items, starting with current and recent years’ acquisitions until all items are covered and thereafter, renew the AREs at least every three years.
